Method Overloading:
ğŸ‘‰ Using the same method name with different parameters in the same class.

Method Overriding:
ğŸ‘‰ Redefining a parent class method in a child class with the same signature.


Diff b/w functions and methods :
ğŸ‘‰ In Java, there are NO standalone functions.
ğŸ‘‰ Everything is a method.
because
A function is A block of code
That exists independently (outside any class)
which is NOT allowed in Java


whereas methods is a block of code that:
Is written inside a class
Is called using an object or class name


