throw is used to manually create and send an exception at runtime when a problem occurs.

throws is used to tell the compiler that a method may throw an exception, and the caller must handle it.
ğŸ‘‰ It does NOT handle the exception
ğŸ‘‰ It only passes the responsibility to the caller

in unchecked exception compiler does not force to handle it.
in checked exception compiler forces to handle it.